title: AREA ROUNDUP: Local divers compete at Canandaigua
text: Posted Oct. 10, 2015 at 10:07 PM By Messenger Post Posted Oct. 10, 2015 at 10:07 PM Canandaigua, N.Y. CANANDAIGUA — Canandaigua hosted the 2015 Diving Invitational on Saturday. The top four girls qualified for states. Canandaigua’s Serica Hallstead placed first and set a new pool record for the Braves. Victor’s Shae Heitz took fourth place and Marcus Whitman’s Victoria Shively finished in fifth place. Celina Lillyquist took seventh place for Canandaigua and Katlin Wells finished in eighth place for Marcus Whitman. In other high school sports action on Saturday: BOYS SOCCER HAC 4, Honeoye 0 Ben Frenett continued his fantastic season with three goals for the Wolves. Frenett scored two first half goals and added his third 20 minutes into the second half. Jamarr Paisley scored the first goal of the game eight minutes in and was assisted by Frenett. Eastridge 2, Pal-Mac 1 Graham Torres and Austin Iodice scored for Eastridge and Stevaughn Service and Jacob Tudisco each had an assist. By Messenger Post
